        <div class="highlight">
            <p><strong>Privacy-First by Design:</strong> QuoteCreator is a local-first mobile application. Your estimate data stays on your device. We do not collect, store, or transmit your business data to any servers.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="toc">
            <h3>Table of Contents</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#overview">Overview</a></li>
                <li><a href="#data-collection">Data Collection</a></li>
                <li><a href="#data-storage">Data Storage</a></li>
                <li><a href="#clio-integration">Clio Integration</a></li>
                <li><a href="#third-party">Third-Party Services</a></li>
                <li><a href="#permissions">Permissions</a></li>
                <li><a href="#data-security">Data Security</a></li>
                <li><a href="#data-deletion">Your Rights & Data Deletion</a></li>
                <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
        <p>QuoteCreator is a professional estimate and quote generation app designed for business professionals. We are committed to protecting your privacy through a local-first architecture that keeps your data under your control.</p>
        <p><strong>Key Privacy Principles:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li>Your estimate data never leaves your device unless you explicitly share it</li>
            <li>No account creation required</li>
            <li>No analytics or tracking services</li>
            <li>No advertisements</li>
            <li>Optional Clio integration uses industry-standard OAuth (you control access)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="data-collection">Data Collection</h2>
        <p><strong>We collect ZERO business data.</strong></p>
        <p>QuoteCreator does not collect or transmit:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Your estimates, quotes, or invoices</li>
            <li>Customer information you enter</li>
            <li>Line items, pricing, or business data</li>
            <li>Company settings or preferences</li>
            <li>Usage analytics or behavioral tracking</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What We Do Collect</h3>
        <p>The only data that leaves your device is:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Payment transaction data:</strong> When you purchase the app via Google Play, Google processes your payment (we never see your credit card details)</li>
            <li><strong>Clio OAuth tokens:</strong> When you connect to Clio (optional), OAuth tokens are stored encrypted on your device and used to authenticate API requests</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="data-storage">Data Storage</h2>
        <p>All business data you create in QuoteCreator is stored <strong>exclusively on your Android device</strong> using SQLite database:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Estimates and quotes</li>
            <li>Line items and pricing</li>
            <li>Customer information (optional)</li>
            <li>Company settings and branding preferences</li>
            <li>Clio OAuth tokens (encrypted, when connected)</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Your data never leaves your device</strong> unless you explicitly:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Generate and share a PDF file using Android's share feature</li>
            <li>Upload an estimate to Clio (optional feature, requires your explicit action)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="clio-integration">Clio Integration</h2>
        <p>QuoteCreator offers optional integration with Clio practice management software. This feature is completely optional and requires your explicit consent.</p>

        <h3>How Clio Integration Works</h3>
        <p>When you connect to Clio:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Secure authentication:</strong> We never see or store your Clio password</li>
            <li><strong>Access tokens:</strong> Encrypted and stored on your device only</li>
            <li><strong>Requested permissions:</strong> "Read matters" and "Write documents" (to browse your matters and upload PDFs)</li>
            <li><strong>Data transmission:</strong> Only when you tap "Upload to Clio" - we send the PDF and matter ID to Clio's API</li>
            <li><strong>Disconnection:</strong> You can disconnect at any time via Settings, which deletes all Clio tokens from your device</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What We Send to Clio</h3>
        <p>Only when you explicitly tap "Upload to Clio":</p>
        <ul>
            <li>The PDF file you generated</li>
            <li>The matter ID you selected</li>
            <li>Document metadata (filename, creation date)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Automatically sync data to Clio</li>
            <li>Upload estimates without your explicit action</li>
            <li>Store copies of uploaded documents on any servers</li>
            <li>Share your Clio data with third parties</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Clio's Privacy Policy</h3>
        <p>When you use Clio integration, you are also subject to <a href="https://www.clio.com/company/privacy-policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Clio's Privacy Policy</a>. Clio is a separate company and we recommend reviewing their policies.</p>

        <h2 id="third-party">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>QuoteCreator uses the following third-party services:</p>

        <h3>Clio (Optional)</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Practice management integration</li>
            <li><strong>Data shared:</strong> Only PDFs you explicitly upload</li>
            <li><strong>Privacy:</strong> <a href="https://www.clio.com/company/privacy-policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Clio Privacy Policy</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Google Play Billing</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> In-app purchase processing ($12.99 one-time payment)</li>
            <li><strong>Data shared:</strong> Payment transaction data (handled by Google)</li>
            <li><strong>Privacy:</strong> <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Local Libraries (No Data Transmission)</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>iText 7 Community:</strong> PDF generation (operates locally, no network calls)</li>
            <li><strong>Jetpack Compose:</strong> Android UI framework (operates locally)</li>
            <li><strong>SQLite:</strong> Local database (operates locally)</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>No analytics, crash reporting, or cloud services.</strong></p>

        <h2 id="permissions">Permissions</h2>
        <p>QuoteCreator requests the following Android permissions:</p>

        <h3>INTERNET</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Clio OAuth authentication and document upload (optional feature)</li>
            <li><strong>Usage:</strong> Only used when you connect to Clio or upload documents</li>
            <li><strong>Background access:</strong> No</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (Android 10 and below)</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Save generated PDF files to your device's Downloads folder</li>
            <li><strong>Usage:</strong> Only when you tap "Generate PDF"</li>
            <li><strong>Data access:</strong> Only writes PDF files you explicitly create</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>MANAGE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (Android 11+)</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Save PDF files to scoped storage (Downloads)</li>
            <li><strong>Usage:</strong> Modern scoped storage - app cannot access other apps' files</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="data-security">Data Security</h2>
        <p>Your data is protected by multiple layers of security:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Device encryption:</strong> All Android 11+ devices encrypt data at rest by default</li>
            <li><strong>Local-only storage:</strong> No cloud sync = no cloud breaches</li>
            <li><strong>Encrypted OAuth tokens:</strong> Clio access tokens stored with Android KeyStore encryption</li>
            <li><strong>HTTPS only:</strong> All Clio API requests use TLS 1.2+ encryption</li>
            <li><strong>No password storage:</strong> We never see or store your Clio password (OAuth handles authentication)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="data-deletion">Your Rights & Data Deletion</h2>

        <h3>Your Rights (GDPR, CCPA, etc.)</h3>
        <p>Under privacy laws like GDPR (EU), CCPA (California), and PIPEDA (Canada), you have rights to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Access your data:</strong> All your data is in your device's app storage (Settings → Apps → QuoteCreator → Storage)</li>
            <li><strong>Delete your data:</strong> Uninstall the app or clear app data (see below)</li>
            <li><strong>Export your data:</strong> Generate PDFs and save to any location you choose</li>
            <li><strong>Opt-out of collection:</strong> Nothing to opt out of - we collect no business data</li>
            <li><strong>Revoke Clio access:</strong> Disconnect Clio in Settings to delete all OAuth tokens</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>How to Delete Your Data</h3>
        <p>To permanently delete all your QuoteCreator data from your device:</p>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Option 1 - Uninstall:</strong> Uninstall QuoteCreator from your device (deletes all app data)</li>
            <li><strong>Option 2 - Clear data:</strong> Android Settings → Apps → QuoteCreator → Storage → Clear Data</li>
        </ol>
        <p>This permanently deletes:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>All estimates and quotes</li>
            <li>All customer information</li>
            <li>All settings and preferences</li>
            <li>Clio OAuth tokens (if connected)</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Note:</strong> PDFs you've already shared or uploaded to Clio are not deleted (they're stored separately on your device or in Clio).</p>

        <h3>Children's Privacy</h3>
        <p>QuoteCreator does not collect data from anyone, including children under 13. The app is designed for business use by adults and is not directed at children.</p>

        <h3>Changes to This Policy</h3>
        <p>If we change our privacy practices, we will:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Update this policy with the new "Last Updated" date</li>
            <li>Announce material changes in app update notes</li>
            <li>For significant changes, request your consent when you update the app</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Legal Compliance</h3>
        <p>QuoteCreator is compliant with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>GDPR</strong> (European Union) - No data processing</li>
            <li><strong>CCPA</strong> (California) - No data sale or collection</li>
            <li><strong>COPPA</strong> (US Children's Privacy) - No child data collection</li>
            <li><strong>PIPEDA</strong> (Canada) - No personal data handling</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="contact">Contact</h2>
        <p>For privacy questions, concerns, or data requests:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@lexopoly.com">support@lexopoly.com</a></li>
            <li><strong>Company:</strong> Lexopoly LLC</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="highlight">
            <p><strong>Summary:</strong> QuoteCreator is a local-first app. Your business data stays on your device. We collect nothing, track nothing, and share nothing unless you explicitly upload to Clio. Privacy by design.</p>
